<h2><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>About The Mag</strong></span></h2>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #000000;">VJs Magazine is an international open-sharing web magazine which deals with audio visual art forms and creative technologies. It was launched in April 2013 by founder Guillaume J. Lauzier. It is accessible to anyone who wants to share, is passionate about or just has a general interest in live audiovisual performances and creative technology. It offers daily news about upcoming and past projects, a section for learning with recommended books and courses, technical reviews and tutorials, interviews with top artists. Check upcoming events in your area with a interactive calendar, anyone is welcome to share through the different forms available on the <span style="color: #3366ff;"><a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/submit/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Submit</span></a></span> page.</span></p>

<h2><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Submitting Content</strong></span></h2>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #000000;">We accept articles, videos or projects, product release information and your app to review, upcoming events or festivals and workshop postings, competitions and vj contest, your reviews and interviews under certain conditions, about new creative technologies, relevant school courses, partnership proposal for cross-promotion and even your help by simply sharing on the submit form. This is not a promise of success, part of your contribution will be a statement on our mag and information for other contributors to read, and you'll have your own profile with your posts and social profiles attached too! <span data-reactid=".9.0.0">We want you to be a part of it, creativity is something we share. ;)</span>
</span></p>

